\Phi\in\mathbb{Z}[X]
p
\Phi = 1 + X + X^2 + \ldots + X^{p-1}
k\in\mathbb{Z}
\varphi
\varphi : \mathbb{Z}/\Phi(k) \to \mathbb{Z}[\zeta]/(k-\zeta),\quad z + (\Phi(k)) \mapsto z+(k-\zeta)
\mathbb{Z}[X] / \langle \Phi(X), X-k \rangle
 \mathbb{Z}[X] / \langle \Phi(X), X-k \rangle \cong (\mathbb{Z}[X] / \Phi(X))/(X-k) \cong \mathbb{Z}[\zeta] / (\zeta - k)
 \mathbb{Z}[X] / \langle \Phi(X), X-k \rangle \cong (\mathbb{Z}[X] / (X-k))/\Phi(X) \cong \mathbb{Z} / \Phi(k)
